  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 14a87f5f6f38bd3439451c3384a31a59, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  notes: The gameobject with this class attached, and that has a Sprite Renderer,
    will create a new gameobject with an AfterImageGroup class attached to it and
    a hardcoded amount of AfterImage classes stored in the group. When the ground
    is created, it will immediately look for the class AfterImageHandler and add
    itself to a List that's then used by that class to set Active all the AfterImages
    stored in each group. I made it like this to avoid the hassle of manually creating
    a bunch of after images and the pain it could be to change them all if I ever
    needed to.
  afterImagePrefab: {fileID: 6966699086694962128, guid: 8a404528287d32a4a88cbc22d34e009f,
    type: 3}
